{"parentUuid": null, "isSidechain": false, "promptId": "prompt-af6a2ff5", "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "Should I migrate all my raw `fetch` calls to React Query, or just the ones that need caching?"}, "uuid": "af6a2ff5-91b1-4dc1-a0b5-d1d4863729fb", "timestamp": "2026-05-11T14:00:30.000Z", "isMeta": false, "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/Users/alex/code/nextjs-app", "sessionId": "edad7770-457f-4573-add4-64e21e4f99b1", "version": "2.0.0", "gitBranch": "main"}
{"parentUuid": "af6a2ff5-91b1-4dc1-a0b5-d1d4863729fb", "isSidechain": false, "message": {"model": "claude-haiku-4-5", "id": "msg_7bf46361-e7b", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Just the ones that need caching, deduping, or refetch-on-focus. One-shot mutations and fire-and-forget side effects don't need it. The rule I use: if two components might want the same data, or if the data is reused on remount within a minute, it goes through React Query. Otherwise `fetch` in a Server Component or a one-off `useEffect` is fine."}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "usage": {"input_tokens": 479, "output_tokens": 129, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 9904}}, "requestId": "req_d4424852-1ab", "type": "assistant", "uuid": "d0302955-b166-44f4-814d-c6d7a3dd1ecf", "timestamp": "2026-05-11T14:00:36.000Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/Users/alex/code/nextjs-app", "sessionId": "edad7770-457f-4573-add4-64e21e4f99b1", "version": "2.0.0", "gitBranch": "main"}
